    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, squeeze your <strong>sausage meat</strong> from the skins into the pan (clean hands is the best way!) and discard the skins</p><p>Break the <strong>sausage meat </strong>up with a wooden spoon and cook for 6-7 min or until golden, crisp and cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>crispy sausage meat</strong></p>",
